cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with activity recognition in videos using deep Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of different network architectures and their performance, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of RNNs and Temporal-ConvNets for extracting spatiotemporal information also falls under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes new network architectures to integrate spatiotemporal information, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
